description: From French coïncider, from Medieval Latin coincidō, from co- + incidō, from in- + cadō.

verbs.description: coincide (third-person singular simple present coincides, present participle coinciding, simple past and past participle coincided) (intransitive)

entries.meaning: To occupy exactly the same space.
To occur at the same time.
examples: The conference will coincide with his vacation.
Our ideas coincide, except in certain areas.
